cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper is about a dataset collected by a fleet of delivery robots equipped with cameras, IMUs, wheel encoders, and lidars for SLAM and visual place recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of computer vision techniques for place recognition, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper proposes metrics for evaluating metric place recognition algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of operating in real-world environments, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category.
